      • stateMachine

        public static StateMachine.Builder stateMachine()
        Represents a StepFunctions state machine. A state machine must have at least one state.
        Returns:
        Builder used to configure a StateMachine.
        See Also:
        https://states-language.net/spec.html#toplevelfields

      • parallelState

        public static ParallelState.Builder parallelState()
        State that allows for parallel execution of Branchs. A Parallel state causes the interpreter to execute each branch starting with the state named in its “StartAt” field, as concurrently as possible, and wait until each branch terminates (reaches a terminal state) before processing the Parallel state's “Next” field.
        Returns:
        Builder used to configure a ParallelState.
        See Also:
        https://states-language.net/spec.html#parallel-state

      • branch

        public static Branch.Builder branch()
        A single branch of parallel execution in a state machine. See ParallelState.
        Returns:
        Builder used to configure a Branch.

      • passState

        public static PassState.Builder passState()
        The Pass State simply passes its input to its output, performing no work. Pass States are useful when constructing and debugging state machines.

        A Pass State MAY have a field named “Result”. If present, its value is treated as the output of a virtual task, and placed as prescribed by the “ResultPath” field, if any, to be passed on to the next state.

        Returns:
        Builder used to configure a PassState.
        See Also:
        https://states-language.net/spec.html#pass-state

      • succeedState

        public static SucceedState.Builder succeedState()
        The Succeed State terminates a state machine successfully. The Succeed State is a useful target for Choice-state branches that don't do anything but terminate the machine.
        Returns:
        Builder used to configure a SucceedState.
        See Also:
        https://states-language.net/spec.html#succeed-state

      • failState

        public static FailState.Builder failState()
        Terminal state that terminates the state machine and marks it as a failure.
        Returns:
        Builder used to configure a FailState.
        See Also:
        https://states-language.net/spec.html#fail-state

      • waitState

        public static WaitState.Builder waitState()
        A Wait state causes the interpreter to delay the machine from continuing for a specified time. The time can be specified as a wait duration, specified in seconds, or an absolute expiry time, specified as an ISO-8601 extended offset date-time format string.
        Returns:
        Builder used to configure a WaitState.
        See Also:
        https://states-language.net/spec.html#wait-state

      • taskState

        public static TaskState.Builder taskState()
        The Task State causes the interpreter to execute the work identified by the state’s “Resource” field.

        Currently allowed resources include Lambda functions and States activities.

        Returns:
        Builder used to configure a TaskState.
        See Also:
        https://states-language.net/spec.html#task-state

      • choiceState

        public static ChoiceState.Builder choiceState()
        A Choice state adds branching logic to a state machine. A Choice state consists of a list of choices, each of which contains a potential transition state and a condition that determines if that choice is evaluated, and a default state that the state machine transitions to if no choice branches are matched.
        Returns:
        Builder used to configure a ChoiceState.
        See Also:

        • choice

          public static Choice.Builder choice()
          Class representing a choice rule to be included in a ChoiceState. A choice consists of a condition and a state that the state machine will transition to if the condition evaluates to true.
          Returns:
          Builder used to configure a Choice.
          See Also:

          • retrier

            public static Retrier.Builder retrier()
            Describes retry behavior for a state. A Retrier consists of a list of error codes that the retrier applies to and parameters controlling the behavior when a retry is performed.
            Returns:
            Builder used to configure a Retrier.
            See Also:
            https://states-language.net/spec.html#errors

          • catcher

            public static Catcher.Builder catcher()
            Catches an error from a ParallelState or a TaskState and transitions into the specified recovery state. The recovery state will receive the error output as input unless otherwise specified by a ResultPath.
            Returns:
            Builder used to configure a Catcher.
            See Also:
            https://states-language.net/spec.html#errors
